overview.banner.description.message: Common concepts and knowledge for both Core Space and eSpace

overview.description.message: Conflux Network is a state-of-the-art public blockchain system designed to address the common issues of scalability, security, and decentralization that challenge many existing blockchain networks. At its core, Conflux utilizes a unique consensus mechanism known as Tree-Graph. This mechanism allows for the parallel processing of blocks and transactions, reducing the time and resources needed for consensus and increasing the overall capacity of the network.

overview.resources.description.message: We have a varied collection of guides, references and examples to help you around anywhere with your Conflux Integration. Deep dive into the different aspects of Conflux Network and make your own customized integration.

home.featureCards.buildOnESpace.descript.message: Conflux eSpace is a fully EVM-compatible blockchain with much lower gas fee and higher TPS than Ethereum, which can enable developers quick build dApps on it.

home.featureCards.buildOnCoreSpace.descr.message: Conflux Core Space is a third-generation decentralized blockchain with ultra-high performance, utilizing an original Tree-Graph ledger structure and the Ghast consensus algorithm. It natively integrates a transaction sponsorship mechanism, offering a novel user experience for both users and developers.

home.featureCards.basic.description.message: Get started with Conflux Network and understand its unique features. Learn about the protocol's hybrid consensus mechanism and fast finality, and how it differs from other blockchain platforms.

home.featureCards.node.description.message: Learn how to run a node on the Conflux Network and become part of the decentralized network. Follow our step-by-step guides to install and configure your node, connect to the network, and start participating in consensus.

home.featureCards.mine.description.message: Learn how to mine CFX on the Conflux Network. Follow our step-by-step guides to install and configure your node, connect to the network, and start mining.
